// SQL injection examples:
// Basic bypass: ' OR '1'='1' --
// Union attack: ' UNION SELECT username,password FROM users --
// Time-based: '; WAITFOR DELAY '00:00:05' --
// Boolean-based: ' AND (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users) > 0 --

// Prevention:
// Use parameterized queries
// Input validation and sanitization
// Least privilege principle
// Web Application Firewall (WAF)

// Common status codes in security testing:
// 200 - Successful request
// 301/302 - Redirects (potential security issues)
// 401 - Authentication required
// 403 - Access denied (forbidden)
// 404 - Not found (information disclosure)
// 500 - Server error (potential vulnerability)

// Security implications:
// 401 - Weak authentication
// 403 - Access control issues
// 500 - Information disclosure
// 429 - Rate limiting bypass

// Common phishing indicators:
// Suspicious URLs (amaz0n.com vs amazon.com)
// Urgent language ("Act now!", "Your account will be closed")
// Requests for sensitive data (passwords, SSN, credit cards)
// Poor grammar and spelling
// Suspicious attachments (.exe, .zip files)

// Protection measures:
// Email filtering and spam detection
// User awareness training
// Multi-factor authentication
// Regular security updates
// Incident response procedures
